          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "D4 makes the per-decision grounding adjudication a work item of the track implementing this ADR, but the briefing defines that adjudication of the six flipped decisions as a manual follow-up that is out of scope for this track's code. As written, downstream planning can treat those unrelated ADR front-matter edits as required implementation work for this track, contradicting the intended scope. Clarify D4 so the current track only changes the precedence/value-object behavior and leaves the six-decision adjudication to the separate manual follow-up.",
